Class Position

  • java.lang.Object
    • libpract.Position

  • public class Position
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an immutable discrete two dimensional position. It is a point in a 2D plane.

      • isAdjacentTo

        public boolean isAdjacentTo(Position other)
        Returns whether this position is next to the given position. Precondition: the given other position is not null.
        Parameters:
        other - the other position
        Returns:
        whether this position is next to the given position. Positions that are diagonally next to each other are also considered adjacent to each other. Examples:
        • (4,4) and (5,4) are adjacent to each other.
        • (4,4) and (5,5) are adjacent to each other.
        • (4,4) and (4,4) are NOT adjacent to each other.
        • (4,4) and (4,6) are NOT adjacent to each other.
        • (4,4) and (3,4) are adjacent to each other.
